major barbara by george bernard shaw events at stanford major barbara by george bernard shaw facebook twitter email print add to calendar directed by pulitzer prize nominated playwright amy freed and ph d candidate ciara murphy from the noble prize and academy award winning playwright of pygmalion and heartbreak house stanford drama presents george bernard shaw's timeless ironic comedy major barbara in the year 1906 major barbara works righteously for the underprivileged at a salvation army shelter until one day a generous but morally dubious donation is made by her estranged father a millionaire weapons manufacturer barbara's father makes a shambles of the morality of liberalism to him the most shameful sin is poverty and the cardinal virtue is prosperity he points to the generative power of his factories and the respectable residences and comfortable lives of his employees which for barbara makes a devastating case for arms trade profits and a whole new set of ideals here is theatre at its theatrical best new york daily news certainly one of shaw's brightest slyest most provocatively outrageous and most timeless comedies new york post when thursday may 19 2011 8 00 pm friday may 20 2011 8 00 pm saturday may 21 2011 8 00 pm sunday may 22 2011 2 00 pm where pigott theater in memorial auditorium map audience general public tags performance drama arts sponsor department of drama contact dramainfo stanford edu admission tickets $5 $15 at http drama stanford edu by phone at 650 725 arts or in person at stanford ticket office in tressider student union permalink http events stanford edu events 276 27683 more info last modified may 10 2011
